content.description: This is probably the [2nd] longest route on the cliff.  Climb past 11 bolts (formerly 6) to a 2 bolt anchor.
content.protection: This originally had 6 bolts. As of July 2014, there are now 11 bolts.
content.location: To the right of the fence there are several routes, this is the rightmost route of this cluster.

content.description:
This is one of the taller climbs.  A run out to the first clip leads to easier climbing, a hollow flake at the top can be avoided by staying on a more direct line into the dihedral at the top.  It is still cleaning up, so wear a helmet.  This route and

Wasted Asparagus

end below a house, so be quiet or use hand signals.
content.location:
It is to the left of

Wasted Asparagus

.  It is the first route one encounters when heading to the right under the fence.

content.description:
Start up past a hanger with a lot of thread showing above the nut.  Climb up past bolts that angle left and then gets steep for the last few bolts before clipping the chains to the left.  This shares an anchor with

Route 1

.
content.location:
This is 20 feet left of

Route 3

.

content.description:
Climb the straight line of black bolts through the steepest section on this chunk of rock.  Climb from the ground and run it out on easy terrain or start on the ledge for

Route 1

, and

0.5

. It is steep and fun with big holds.  If memory serves me, it uses the last bolt of

Route 1

before the anchor.
content.protection: 5 or 6 bolts to a 2 bolt anchor.
content.location:
This is just right of

Route 1

.  It shares anchor with

Route 1

and

Route 2

.

content.description: Climb up bolts angling right through slightly overhanging rock.  It has plenty of positive holds, though it is a little chossy and is very enjoyable.
content.protection:
Bolts with rusty nuts to chains shared with

Route 2

.  Bring a helmet.
content.location:
Start on a ledge left of

Route 2

.

content.description:
Start up

Route 1

, clip the bolt with rust and move left through pockets to a shiny bolt.  Follow this line 6 or seven bolts to anchor.  This has clean rock with a slabby crux.
content.location:
It is left of

Route 1

and shares the first bolt with it.
